1
00:00:07,721 --> 00:00:09,481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

2
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:41,258
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

3
00:00:41,258 --> 00:00:43,838
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

4
00:00:56,638 --> 00:00:58,772
Did I hear that wrong?

5
00:01:21,005 --> 00:01:22,772
Aren't you gonna keep humming?

6
00:01:24,938 --> 00:01:28,405
At first, it was just about
scaring people a little.

7
00:01:29,772 --> 00:01:33,538
But I kind of liked it
when people were afraid of me.

8
00:01:33,538 --> 00:01:36,405
Like I've become someone important.

9
00:01:37,272 --> 00:01:41,705
Then, was there a first incident
that led you to commit murder?

10
00:01:41,705 --> 00:01:45,372
What's wrong with today?

11
00:01:45,372 --> 00:01:49,972
It all started with just a stone.

12
00:01:49,972 --> 00:01:51,738
Who is there?

13
00:01:58,972 --> 00:02:01,405
Is anyone there?

14
00:02:08,738 --> 00:02:11,905
If I hadn't been hit by that stone,

15
00:02:11,905 --> 00:02:14,601
or if I hadn't been seen,

16
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:16,169
would things have been different?

17
00:02:18,105 --> 00:02:21,338
It started by accident,

18
00:02:21,338 --> 00:02:24,005
but it also feels like my fate.

19
00:02:24,638 --> 00:02:26,569
Have you

20
00:02:26,569 --> 00:02:31,241
ever been found out as the killer?

21
00:02:33,472 --> 00:02:34,972
I guess not.

22
00:02:34,972 --> 00:02:39,405
If I had, I wouldn't have gotten away
with it this long, right?

23
00:02:39,405 --> 00:02:41,872
Don't you agree?

24
00:02:51,005 --> 00:02:52,505
Here, please have some.

25
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:55,072
Wow, thank you!

26
00:02:55,072 --> 00:02:56,572
[Episode 7]
You are Seok Man's sister-in-law, right?

27
00:02:56,572 --> 00:02:58,438
He works at my house,

28
00:02:58,438 --> 00:03:00,738
but now we're just like siblings.

29
00:03:00,738 --> 00:03:03,472
I thought you were siblings
since you always took such good care of him.

30
00:03:03,472 --> 00:03:04,872
Oh, family is nothing special.

31
00:03:04,872 --> 00:03:07,238
If you live together like this,
everyone becomes family.

32
00:03:07,238 --> 00:03:09,505
Still, I feel bad for Seok Man.

33
00:03:09,505 --> 00:03:12,372
His family scattered everywhere
looking for work.

34
00:03:12,372 --> 00:03:15,705
He came here when he was about eighteen.

35
00:03:16,805 --> 00:03:21,072
Do you happen to know
when he started limping?

36
00:03:21,072 --> 00:03:24,505
I heard he had polio when he was young.

37
00:03:25,405 --> 00:03:26,405
So he can't run?

38
00:03:26,405 --> 00:03:29,105
Oh dear, how could he run with those legs?

39
00:03:29,105 --> 00:03:33,105
Even walking is hard for him,
as he's always unsteady.

40
00:03:41,205 --> 00:03:44,738
When we get to the hospital,
behave and get treated properly.

41
00:03:44,738 --> 00:03:46,872
Don't cause trouble.

42
00:03:47,572 --> 00:03:49,172
Alright.

43
00:03:54,697 --> 00:03:55,721
[Police]

44
00:04:08,872 --> 00:04:11,805
- What is this?
- We're from the prosecutor's office.

45
00:04:11,805 --> 00:04:14,305
We're here to transfer
Lee Ki Beom to the detention center.

46
00:04:14,305 --> 00:04:16,572
Pardon?

47
00:04:16,572 --> 00:04:18,138
We haven't received any notice about that.

48
00:04:18,138 --> 00:04:19,938
Then check with the station.

49
00:04:19,938 --> 00:04:22,472
- What are you waiting for? Get him out.
- Yes, sir.

50
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:25,505
Wait a minute!

51
00:04:25,505 --> 00:04:27,272
Wait!

52
00:04:29,705 --> 00:04:32,372
Who gave you permission for this? Huh?

53
00:04:32,372 --> 00:04:35,272
You can't just do this all of a sudden! Wait!

54
00:04:41,038 --> 00:04:43,372
Lee Ki Beom has been safely
transferred to the detention center.

55
00:04:43,372 --> 00:04:44,572
[Kangseng, Muwon]
Visitations are also banned.

56
00:04:44,572 --> 00:04:47,138
Alright, thank you for your hard work.

57
00:04:47,138 --> 00:04:49,338
You can head home from there.

58
00:04:51,238 --> 00:04:54,372
No need to worry.
I've taken care of everything.

59
00:04:54,372 --> 00:04:56,738
Thank you for your help!

60
00:04:56,738 --> 00:04:59,872
I told you, you shouldn't beat him so badly.

61
00:04:59,872 --> 00:05:04,172
I just lost my temper
when I heard you were attacked, sir.

62
00:05:06,872 --> 00:05:11,905
Wow, I didn't know
you guys cared about me this much.

63
00:05:12,572 --> 00:05:15,472
Well, if that's the reason,

64
00:05:15,472 --> 00:05:17,513
I should

65
00:05:17,513 --> 00:05:19,772
take responsibility
for both of you till the end.

66
00:05:19,772 --> 00:05:21,605
Thank you!

67
00:05:22,672 --> 00:05:23,938
Get back to your work.

68
00:05:23,938 --> 00:05:27,405
Yes, I'll get going, sir.

69
00:05:34,372 --> 00:05:36,305
Thank you!

70
00:05:44,505 --> 00:05:47,572
Hey, is this really
something to be thankful for?

71
00:05:47,572 --> 00:05:50,205
That punk made us do everything.

72
00:05:55,038 --> 00:05:56,105
Listen.

73
00:05:56,809 --> 00:05:58,638
Watch what you say.

74
00:05:58,638 --> 00:06:02,838
If either of us mentions Prosecutor Cha,
we're both done.

75
00:06:04,138 --> 00:06:05,838
Keep that in mind.

76
00:06:17,705 --> 00:06:20,105
Seok Man, now,

77
00:06:21,305 --> 00:06:24,972
do you remember the faces
of the detectives who arrested Ki Beom?

78
00:06:26,605 --> 00:06:27,672
Yeah.

79
00:06:27,672 --> 00:06:29,672
Point them out for me.

80
00:06:31,672 --> 00:06:33,438
[Investigation Division]
These two here.

81
00:06:33,438 --> 00:06:36,672
Jang Myeong Do, Do Hyeong Gu.

82
00:06:40,772 --> 00:06:43,872
You knew Ki Beom's family
was looking for him.

83
00:06:43,872 --> 00:06:45,272
But why didn't you say anything?

84
00:06:45,272 --> 00:06:48,605
They said they wouldn't
let me off if I talked.

85
00:06:48,605 --> 00:06:53,038
So these two are the ones who threatened you?

86
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:54,872
Yeah.

87
00:07:04,372 --> 00:07:06,072
But Seok Man,

88
00:07:07,538 --> 00:07:09,972
why were you there that day?

89
00:07:09,972 --> 00:07:12,238
I mean, around Lee Joo Hee's place.

90
00:07:12,238 --> 00:07:14,038
And at that hour,

91
00:07:14,038 --> 00:07:16,772
with your bad leg.

92
00:07:17,705 --> 00:07:19,472
Well, that's...

93
00:07:23,172 --> 00:07:27,205
I don't really remember. Is that important?

94
00:07:29,472 --> 00:07:31,438
That's okay.

95
00:07:32,238 --> 00:07:33,805
That can happen.

96
00:07:33,805 --> 00:07:36,472
I forget things all the time.

97
00:07:43,005 --> 00:07:48,972
[Kangseng Police Station]

98
00:07:49,705 --> 00:07:51,605
Thank you for all the trouble.

99
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:54,072
It's nothing.

100
00:07:58,338 --> 00:07:59,972
Seok Man.

101
00:07:59,972 --> 00:08:02,838
What kind of guy is Ki Beom, in your opinion?

102
00:08:02,838 --> 00:08:05,449
- Ki Beom?
- Yeah.

103
00:08:05,449 --> 00:08:07,110
Well,

104
00:08:08,205 --> 00:08:11,738
he's good-looking, kind,

105
00:08:11,738 --> 00:08:14,372
and popular with women.

106
00:08:15,105 --> 00:08:17,405
But what makes you ask?

107
00:08:17,405 --> 00:08:21,338
It feels like someone
is deliberately framing him.

108
00:08:21,338 --> 00:08:24,238
Like they hold a grudge against him.

109
00:08:24,238 --> 00:08:26,505
Anyone comes to mind?

110
00:08:27,638 --> 00:08:31,072
There are a few guys who pick fights
with Ki Beom sometimes.

111
00:08:31,072 --> 00:08:32,872
What kind of guys?

112
00:08:33,872 --> 00:08:38,238
They say he flirts with all the women
in the neighborhood.

113
00:08:38,238 --> 00:08:42,505
I guess they're jealous
because Ki Beom is so popular.

114
00:08:43,337 --> 00:08:48,138
That's ridiculous, don't you think?

115
00:08:49,838 --> 00:08:51,638
I should get going now.

116
00:08:51,638 --> 00:08:52,672
Okay.

117
00:08:52,672 --> 00:08:54,638
Sorry, I can't even take you home.

118
00:08:54,638 --> 00:08:56,838
It's fine. I'll just take the bus.

119
00:08:56,838 --> 00:08:58,438
Alright.

120
00:09:29,605 --> 00:09:32,405
What are you doing here?

121
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:34,772
Your daughter-in-law made me promise
before she left.

122
00:09:34,772 --> 00:09:36,238
She told me to make sure
you take your medicine.

123
00:09:36,238 --> 00:09:38,805
She had no one else to ask,
so she came to you?

124
00:09:38,805 --> 00:09:41,438
Forget it. Take that away.

125
00:09:41,438 --> 00:09:44,438
You don't need to do this anymore.

126
00:09:44,438 --> 00:09:46,972
We're nothing to each other now.

127
00:09:50,605 --> 00:09:53,138
Even if you hate me,
please take your medicine.

128
00:09:55,072 --> 00:09:59,972
Everyone is blaming Ki Beom.
Are you just going to lie here?

129
00:10:00,772 --> 00:10:04,872
We should tell them that Ki Beom
isn't like that, and he's innocent.

130
00:10:04,872 --> 00:10:08,538
If they don't believe us,
we'll say it a thousand times.

131
00:10:09,472 --> 00:10:11,505
It's too much for me to handle it alone.

132
00:10:11,505 --> 00:10:14,538
So please, get your strength back.

133
00:10:16,572 --> 00:10:18,305
Here.

134
00:10:52,105 --> 00:10:55,972
[Witness Statement Record]

135
00:10:55,972 --> 00:10:59,505
With a statement like this,
Lee Ki Beom could be found not guilty.

136
00:10:59,505 --> 00:11:04,072
Please open an internal investigation
into Jang Myeong Do and Do Hyeong Gu.

137
00:11:04,072 --> 00:11:07,972
We can't even question the victim,
and you want an internal investigation?

138
00:11:07,972 --> 00:11:10,472
We can't question the victim?
What do you mean?

139
00:11:10,472 --> 00:11:15,105
Today, Lee Ki Beom was transferred to
the detention center. No visits permitted.

140
00:11:15,872 --> 00:11:18,872
Si Young was one step ahead of us.

141
00:11:18,872 --> 00:11:23,172
So why would you reveal
your hand to the enemy like that?

142
00:11:23,172 --> 00:11:26,921
Ugh, jeez...

143
00:11:28,905 --> 00:11:32,538
What now? We already took a hit like that.

144
00:11:32,538 --> 00:11:35,172
Want me to tell you that punk's weakness?

145
00:11:37,372 --> 00:11:39,705
Why would I turn it down?

146
00:11:42,038 --> 00:11:44,105
Come here, closer.

147
00:11:44,105 --> 00:11:48,072
I shouldn't be saying this as his brother,
but I feel bad for you, so I'll tell you.

148
00:11:50,105 --> 00:11:52,305
He's

149
00:11:52,305 --> 00:11:54,638
basically still a kid.

150
00:11:54,638 --> 00:11:57,801
He's still scared of his father.

151
00:11:57,801 --> 00:12:03,172
He'll do anything to
avoid disappointing his father.

152
00:12:09,172 --> 00:12:11,405
[Kangseng Daily]

153
00:12:11,405 --> 00:12:12,772
Wait, is that true?

154
00:12:12,772 --> 00:12:14,638
Yes, we secured a witness.

155
00:12:14,638 --> 00:12:17,005
Illegal arrest, and even the victim's purse.

156
00:12:17,005 --> 00:12:19,972
If that's true, then Ki Beom
might not be the real killer.

157
00:12:19,972 --> 00:12:24,038
Actually, Lee Ki Beom confessed to
everything the day he was arrested.

158
00:12:24,038 --> 00:12:25,705
Was he tortured or something?

159
00:12:25,705 --> 00:12:27,238
I knew it.

160
00:12:27,238 --> 00:12:30,772
Ki Beom isn't the kind of guy
who could kill someone.

161
00:12:31,738 --> 00:12:34,038
We should break the news first.

162
00:12:34,038 --> 00:12:35,705
Think this through.

163
00:12:35,705 --> 00:12:38,738
But if Lee Ki Beom is the real killer,
we'll face backlash.

164
00:12:38,738 --> 00:12:41,905
We still have to report it.
That's what journalists do.

165
00:12:41,905 --> 00:12:43,305
Ji Won!

166
00:12:43,305 --> 00:12:44,938
Yeah.

167
00:12:44,938 --> 00:12:46,272
Someone came to see you.

168
00:12:46,272 --> 00:12:48,005
Who?

169
00:12:52,805 --> 00:12:54,072
Do what?

170
00:12:54,072 --> 00:12:55,205
A favor.

171
00:12:55,205 --> 00:12:58,305
[Kangseng Daily]
Just add one sentence to your article.

172
00:12:58,305 --> 00:13:02,572
"The special investigation team
has found another prime suspect."

173
00:13:04,272 --> 00:13:06,138
First of all, is that even true?

174
00:13:07,405 --> 00:13:09,238
Who is that?

175
00:13:10,572 --> 00:13:13,572
I can't reveal that yet.

176
00:13:17,072 --> 00:13:18,872
Don't worry. I'm not bluffing.

177
00:13:18,872 --> 00:13:22,338
If you can't even reveal it, why publish it?

178
00:13:22,338 --> 00:13:24,305
Ki Beom's been locked up in the detention.

179
00:13:24,305 --> 00:13:26,305
Visitation is banned,
so I can't even see him.

180
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:28,105
- What?
- They've completely silenced him,

181
00:13:28,105 --> 00:13:30,405
so we can't even start the investigation.

182
00:13:30,405 --> 00:13:33,705
Now Ki Beom can't get out
based only on Im Seok Man's testimony.

183
00:13:33,705 --> 00:13:35,438
This is insane.

184
00:13:35,438 --> 00:13:37,472
If we say a new suspect has appeared,

185
00:13:37,472 --> 00:13:39,838
they won't be able to
treat Ki Beom recklessly like before.

186
00:13:39,838 --> 00:13:42,772
Because they might think
he's not the real killer.

187
00:13:42,772 --> 00:13:47,338
So you're saying you didn't even
report the suspect to the police?

188
00:13:50,738 --> 00:13:53,338
The suspect is Im Seok Man, right?

189
00:13:55,572 --> 00:13:57,138
That's right, huh?

190
00:13:57,138 --> 00:14:00,138
I had a bad feeling when you kept asking
whether he could run or not.

191
00:14:00,138 --> 00:14:03,405
First Ki Beom, then Ki Hwan,
and now Seok Man?

192
00:14:04,338 --> 00:14:06,738
Is this because of Park Ae Sook's purse?
That's why you suspect Seok Man?

193
00:14:06,738 --> 00:14:08,105
There's even more.

194
00:14:08,105 --> 00:14:11,838
Ki Beom was arrested in front of
Lee Joo Hee's place, where she was killed.

195
00:14:11,838 --> 00:14:14,638
And Seok Man witnessed it,

196
00:14:14,638 --> 00:14:17,638
meaning he was there
at the time of the murder.

197
00:14:17,638 --> 00:14:19,205
But Seok Man's limping...

198
00:14:19,205 --> 00:14:21,205
So,

199
00:14:21,205 --> 00:14:22,305
I'm going to check it out.

200
00:14:22,305 --> 00:14:23,838
Check out what?

201
00:14:23,838 --> 00:14:25,205
Whether he can run or not?

202
00:14:25,205 --> 00:14:26,772
No.

203
00:14:26,772 --> 00:14:28,805
Even if he can't run,

204
00:14:28,805 --> 00:14:30,772
whether he could still commit the crime.

205
00:14:30,772 --> 00:14:33,438
That day, the killer definitely chased me.

206
00:14:33,438 --> 00:14:35,605
Did you see him running?

207
00:14:36,438 --> 00:14:38,838
Of course he ran, if he was chasing me.

208
00:14:38,838 --> 00:14:40,438
He hit me with a rock.

209
00:14:40,438 --> 00:14:41,838
What if he threw it instead?

210
00:14:41,838 --> 00:14:44,905
You're making a big story out of this.

211
00:14:44,905 --> 00:14:47,538
Don't worry. I won't act rashly.

212
00:14:47,538 --> 00:14:49,838
I'm going to check every step carefully.

213
00:14:49,838 --> 00:14:51,625
Until then,

214
00:14:51,625 --> 00:14:54,972
the suspect's identity
will be kept strictly confidential.

215
00:14:54,972 --> 00:14:57,138
Please write the article.

216
00:14:57,138 --> 00:14:58,793
Even if I can't show my hand,

217
00:14:58,793 --> 00:15:02,605
they need to know
theirs might be a losing one.

218
00:15:11,538 --> 00:15:12,972
What did Tae Joo say?

219
00:15:12,972 --> 00:15:14,705
Did he tell you not to publish the article?

220
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:16,438
Do you have a ball or something?

221
00:15:16,438 --> 00:15:18,238
A ball?

222
00:15:18,238 --> 00:15:21,605
Stand here for a moment, okay?

223
00:15:21,605 --> 00:15:25,905
When I give the signal, throw this. Got it?

224
00:15:25,905 --> 00:15:28,238
Hit you with this? Won't it hurt?

225
00:15:28,238 --> 00:15:30,438
Talk after you hit me.

226
00:15:30,438 --> 00:15:32,205
Okay.

227
00:15:32,205 --> 00:15:35,605
Start!

228
00:15:35,605 --> 00:15:37,705
One,

229
00:15:37,705 --> 00:15:39,338
two,

230
00:15:39,338 --> 00:15:41,205
three,

231
00:15:41,205 --> 00:15:43,038
four,

232
00:15:43,038 --> 00:15:45,338
five... now!

233
00:15:57,372 --> 00:15:59,305
Ji Won...

234
00:16:10,705 --> 00:16:14,138
Ji Won, what happened?

235
00:16:14,138 --> 00:16:15,838
Did it hit you?

236
00:16:17,138 --> 00:16:19,338
You...

237
00:16:19,338 --> 00:16:20,705
What?

238
00:16:20,705 --> 00:16:22,372
It hit, huh?

239
00:16:23,472 --> 00:16:26,572
I... almost got hit.

240
00:16:27,905 --> 00:16:30,205
Darn it.

241
00:16:30,205 --> 00:16:32,238
That actually works?

242
00:16:40,205 --> 00:16:42,038
Yeah?

243
00:16:42,038 --> 00:16:44,205
Right.

244
00:16:44,205 --> 00:16:48,372
Have the rest join
the special investigation team as planned.

245
00:16:50,705 --> 00:16:52,572
Why bring in a special investigation team?

246
00:16:52,572 --> 00:16:55,505
The case is basically wrapped up.
Is it necessary?

247
00:16:55,505 --> 00:16:57,472
At Kang Tae Joo's request.

248
00:16:57,472 --> 00:16:58,505
What?

249
00:16:58,505 --> 00:17:03,038
I thought you two were friends.
Guess you're not that close.

250
00:17:16,038 --> 00:17:17,321
[Real killer caught, or a forced confession?]
A prime suspect

251
00:17:17,321 --> 00:17:19,005
in the Kangseng serial killings, Mr. Lee,

252
00:17:19,005 --> 00:17:22,738
has been found to have been illegally
arrested by the police, sparking controversy.

253
00:17:22,738 --> 00:17:25,805
It has been confirmed that he was
actually apprehended five days earlier

254
00:17:25,805 --> 00:17:27,905
- than the arrest date announced by police.
- Where's Prosecutor Cha?

255
00:17:27,905 --> 00:17:29,865
- He stepped out for a moment.
- What he went through during that time

256
00:17:29,865 --> 00:17:31,238
remains unknown.

257
00:17:31,238 --> 00:17:33,972
Mr. Lee confessed all crimes
immediately after arrest,

258
00:17:33,972 --> 00:17:38,838
but there are suspicions he was
coerced or abused during detention.

259
00:17:38,838 --> 00:17:41,438
If it's revealed as a coerced confession,

260
00:17:41,438 --> 00:17:43,605
the repercussions will be even greater.

261
00:17:43,605 --> 00:17:48,438
Meanwhile, a newly formed task force
has identified another key suspect,

262
00:17:48,438 --> 00:17:51,738
so the focus is on which of the two suspects
is the real killer.

263
00:17:51,738 --> 00:17:54,138
Put together the internal audit team.

264
00:17:54,138 --> 00:17:56,372
Immediately!

265
00:18:00,372 --> 00:18:03,505
[Real killer caught, or a forced confession?]
"Another prime suspect?"

266
00:18:05,205 --> 00:18:08,205
That punk's even hiding his cards from me?

267
00:18:08,205 --> 00:18:10,972
The police announced they will
use the latest forensic techniques

268
00:18:10,972 --> 00:18:14,138
to identify the real killer.

269
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:28,238
Detective Kang!

270
00:18:28,972 --> 00:18:30,805
I need to talk to you.

271
00:18:34,005 --> 00:18:37,172
A prime suspect even the prosecutor
doesn't know about?

272
00:18:38,338 --> 00:18:41,872
"Prime suspect"? We're investigating
because there's suspicion.

273
00:18:41,872 --> 00:18:43,572
Anyway, Ms. Seo's been
hearing things somewhere...

274
00:18:43,572 --> 00:18:44,605
Why didn't you report it?

275
00:18:44,605 --> 00:18:46,638
There's no concrete evidence yet.

276
00:18:46,638 --> 00:18:48,405
Cut the crap, you punk!

277
00:18:48,405 --> 00:18:49,772
You think I don't know you?

278
00:18:49,772 --> 00:18:52,372
Once you feel suspicious,
you just charge ahead.

279
00:18:52,372 --> 00:18:54,238
And I end up regretting it.

280
00:18:54,238 --> 00:18:56,705
Feels like I'm the one
who put Ki Beom in this mess.

281
00:18:56,705 --> 00:19:00,138
I actually learn from my mistakes,
unlike someone.

282
00:19:02,038 --> 00:19:04,005
Who is the suspect?

283
00:19:05,672 --> 00:19:07,805
I'll tell you when the investigation is over.

284
00:19:11,872 --> 00:19:13,338
Then what is this?

285
00:19:13,338 --> 00:19:15,538
"New forensic techniques." What's that about?

286
00:19:15,538 --> 00:19:16,572
Oh, that?

287
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:17,938
That's not fully verified, either.

288
00:19:17,938 --> 00:19:21,438
Are you kidding me?

289
00:19:21,438 --> 00:19:24,005
What are you up to?

290
00:19:24,838 --> 00:19:26,472
What do you mean?

291
00:19:26,472 --> 00:19:30,738
I said I'd investigate properly
and report back, Prosecutor Cha.

292
00:19:30,738 --> 00:19:32,805
Just wait quietly.

293
00:19:32,805 --> 00:19:35,272
I only need to check just one thing.

294
00:19:35,272 --> 00:19:37,705
- "Just one thing"?
- Yeah.

295
00:19:37,705 --> 00:19:39,472
Just one thing.

296
00:19:43,005 --> 00:19:45,805
Oh, let me check one thing now.

297
00:19:45,805 --> 00:19:49,372
When you got stabbed,
did you see anything about the suspect?

298
00:19:49,372 --> 00:19:52,905
Like, was there anything
memorable about his walk?

299
00:19:52,905 --> 00:19:55,272
I don't know, darn it!

300
00:20:01,738 --> 00:20:03,672
Just one thing?

301
00:20:10,305 --> 00:20:11,905
- Sir!
- Yeah.

302
00:20:11,905 --> 00:20:13,272
Did you check it out?

303
00:20:13,272 --> 00:20:14,905
Yes.

304
00:20:14,905 --> 00:20:16,805
Im Seok Man is type B.

305
00:20:16,805 --> 00:20:20,338
[Medical Record, Im Seok Man, Type B]

306
00:20:22,138 --> 00:20:24,505
- Okay, let's go!
- Yes, sir.

307
00:20:26,805 --> 00:20:30,305
Now that it's exposed in the press,
an internal audit is unavoidable.

308
00:20:30,305 --> 00:20:32,638
What about keeping
the detectives' mouths shut?

309
00:20:32,638 --> 00:20:34,772
You don't need to worry.

310
00:20:34,772 --> 00:20:37,372
They won't bring me up.

311
00:20:41,405 --> 00:20:43,113
It so happens that

312
00:20:43,113 --> 00:20:45,672
your mother's condition has worsened.

313
00:20:46,838 --> 00:20:49,105
Take some time off for now.

314
00:20:49,105 --> 00:20:51,572
And stay out of any trouble.

315
00:20:54,921 --> 00:20:57,805
- But...
- About the audit,

316
00:20:57,805 --> 00:21:00,572
I'll wrap it up as quickly as possible.

317
00:21:00,572 --> 00:21:03,572
You're lucky you have your brother.

318
00:21:03,572 --> 00:21:06,372
How long are you going to rely on him?

319
00:21:12,505 --> 00:21:13,505
You're leaving?

320
00:21:13,505 --> 00:21:16,838
Yeah, I have to. I've got a mountain of work.

321
00:21:17,638 --> 00:21:19,272
My mother...

322
00:21:22,205 --> 00:21:24,305
Is she very ill?

323
00:21:37,372 --> 00:21:39,038
- Oh, you're here.
- Hello.

324
00:21:39,038 --> 00:21:41,638
Please put them somewhere visible.

325
00:21:41,638 --> 00:21:44,572
Oh my, your son brought you
beautiful flowers.

326
00:21:44,572 --> 00:21:46,805
I'll go put them in a vase.

327
00:21:47,838 --> 00:21:49,438
Mother.

328
00:21:51,038 --> 00:21:52,772
I'm here.

329
00:21:53,938 --> 00:21:56,072
Oh? Oh, dear.

330
00:21:56,072 --> 00:21:58,938
My baby's here?

331
00:21:58,938 --> 00:22:02,172
Si Young, where's your report card?

332
00:22:03,438 --> 00:22:06,605
Your grades didn't drop, right?

333
00:22:06,605 --> 00:22:09,605
You don't need to worry about that anymore.

334
00:22:10,238 --> 00:22:12,838
Si Young,

335
00:22:12,838 --> 00:22:15,705
don't go against your father.

336
00:22:15,705 --> 00:22:20,105
Your father is a scary man.

337
00:22:20,105 --> 00:22:25,272
He's the kind of person
who would kick you and me out.

338
00:22:25,272 --> 00:22:28,872
Mom, I'm a prosecutor.

339
00:22:28,872 --> 00:22:31,005
A prosecutor of the Republic of Korea.

340
00:22:31,005 --> 00:22:32,872
No one can treat me recklessly.

341
00:22:32,872 --> 00:22:35,005
Not even my father.

342
00:22:38,838 --> 00:22:41,005
And I'm getting married.

343
00:22:41,005 --> 00:22:43,105
To a daughter from a very prestigious family.

344
00:22:43,105 --> 00:22:44,772
Oh, dear.

345
00:22:44,772 --> 00:22:48,138
Oh my, thank you.

346
00:22:48,138 --> 00:22:52,305
Oh my, thank you. Thank you.

347
00:22:52,305 --> 00:22:55,038
Oh goodness, thank you.

348
00:22:55,038 --> 00:22:57,705
Please be at ease, Mom.

349
00:22:57,705 --> 00:22:59,438
Don't worry about anything.

350
00:22:59,438 --> 00:23:00,705
Okay.

351
00:23:00,705 --> 00:23:04,372
Oh my, thank you.

352
00:23:05,872 --> 00:23:08,138
Oh, thank you.

353
00:23:08,138 --> 00:23:11,238
Do you admit to the illegal arrest
of Lee Ki Beom?

354
00:23:11,238 --> 00:23:12,838
I told you already.

355
00:23:12,838 --> 00:23:14,905
I wasn't trying to illegally arrest him,

356
00:23:14,905 --> 00:23:20,969
but the prosecutor in charge was
in critical condition, so we had no choice!

357
00:23:23,172 --> 00:23:26,172
We didn't even know
when the prosecutor would wake up.

358
00:23:26,172 --> 00:23:28,505
And if the 48-hour
emergency detention limit passed,

359
00:23:28,505 --> 00:23:30,672
what would happen to the suspect?

360
00:23:30,672 --> 00:23:32,972
Are we just supposed to release him?

361
00:23:32,972 --> 00:23:35,238
What did you do while detaining him?

362
00:23:35,238 --> 00:23:36,305
Did you torture him or something?

363
00:23:36,305 --> 00:23:38,572
Torture? We just asked him questions.

364
00:23:38,572 --> 00:23:42,072
- You verbally abused him, right?
- Let's not be harsh on fellow detectives.

365
00:23:42,072 --> 00:23:47,272
Honestly, you know you have to shout a bit
and make things tense to get people to talk.

366
00:23:48,009 --> 00:23:49,786
Jeez...

367
00:23:53,072 --> 00:23:56,138
Seok Man, I steamed some potatoes.
Feed the kids and take care of the laundry.

368
00:23:56,138 --> 00:23:57,505
Yes, take care!

369
00:23:57,505 --> 00:23:58,872
Girls, Mom's heading out for a bit.

370
00:23:58,872 --> 00:24:02,038
- Bye, Mom!
- Okay.

371
00:24:17,938 --> 00:24:21,505
Hey girls, are you hungry?

372
00:24:21,505 --> 00:24:24,205
Want some potatoes?

373
00:24:25,872 --> 00:24:28,338
Kyeong Jin! I told you not to scribble here!

374
00:24:28,338 --> 00:24:31,072
This belongs to my friend!

375
00:24:31,072 --> 00:24:33,872
- Stop, don't cry.
- Uncle, I hate you.

376
00:24:33,872 --> 00:24:36,372
I'm sorry.

377
00:24:38,272 --> 00:24:41,938
You're hungry, right?
Should we eat some potatoes?

378
00:24:59,138 --> 00:25:00,738
Oh, it's hot!

379
00:25:00,738 --> 00:25:02,205
Me too, me too!

380
00:25:02,205 --> 00:25:04,205
I want to climb up too!

381
00:25:04,205 --> 00:25:05,772
Come on up, come on up!

382
00:25:05,772 --> 00:25:08,338
Girls, let's eat potatoes!

383
00:25:17,438 --> 00:25:19,572
Su Jin!

384
00:25:32,272 --> 00:25:34,372
Su Jin, are you okay? Are you hurt?

385
00:25:34,372 --> 00:25:35,538
No.

386
00:25:35,538 --> 00:25:37,972
Wow, Uncle is super fast.

387
00:25:37,972 --> 00:25:41,338
Of course, I'm really good at running.

388
00:25:44,338 --> 00:25:47,505
I told you not to climb dangerous places!

389
00:25:48,738 --> 00:25:50,938
I won't do it again.

390
00:25:50,938 --> 00:25:53,172
Promise!

391
00:25:53,172 --> 00:25:55,772
Promise!

392
00:25:55,772 --> 00:25:58,972
You must stay safe and grow up strong.

393
00:25:58,972 --> 00:26:02,072
So you can grow up fast and marry me someday.

394
00:26:21,972 --> 00:26:24,305
What brings you here again?

395
00:26:24,305 --> 00:26:28,038
Seok Man, you're type B, right?

396
00:26:28,738 --> 00:26:30,172
Yes.

397
00:26:30,172 --> 00:26:33,872
Oh, what should I do?

398
00:26:33,872 --> 00:26:38,005
I think I'm going to have to ask you
for an embarrassing favor.

399
00:26:39,305 --> 00:26:40,872
What kind of favor?

400
00:26:40,872 --> 00:26:44,538
Well, take off your underwear.

401
00:26:44,538 --> 00:26:46,238
What?

402
00:26:47,605 --> 00:26:49,472
Underwear.

403
00:26:54,605 --> 00:26:56,638
Deliver this to Dr. Jo right away.

404
00:26:56,638 --> 00:26:58,438
Yes, sir.

405
00:26:59,738 --> 00:27:02,005
[Hair of an unidentified suspect]

406
00:27:02,005 --> 00:27:06,572
But how did you get him
to take off his underwear?

407
00:27:06,572 --> 00:27:08,438
Are you curious?

408
00:27:10,238 --> 00:27:12,105
I begged him.

409
00:27:12,105 --> 00:27:14,638
How did you get him to do it?

410
00:27:14,638 --> 00:27:16,438
"The higher-ups set a quota.

411
00:27:16,438 --> 00:27:19,938
We each have to collect
pubic hair from 20 B-type men.

412
00:27:19,938 --> 00:27:22,505
Please help me out."

413
00:27:22,505 --> 00:27:24,805
He actually took off
his underwear? The suspect?

414
00:27:24,805 --> 00:27:26,905
I said the killer's the one who won't do it.

415
00:27:26,905 --> 00:27:28,638
Come on.

416
00:27:28,638 --> 00:27:31,038
Are you type B?
Want to take off your underwear?

417
00:27:31,038 --> 00:27:32,172
Want me to pull your hair out?

418
00:27:32,172 --> 00:27:34,038
Hurry up, you punk!

419
00:27:34,038 --> 00:27:36,605
And tell them to contact me
as soon as the results are out.

420
00:27:36,605 --> 00:27:38,805
- Yes, understood.
- Yeah.

421
00:27:48,738 --> 00:27:50,872
What is this?

422
00:27:50,872 --> 00:27:52,372
Give it here!

423
00:27:52,372 --> 00:27:53,872
Hold on.

424
00:27:53,872 --> 00:27:55,738
Unidentified suspect...

425
00:27:55,738 --> 00:27:57,405
Is there an unidentified suspect?

426
00:27:57,405 --> 00:27:59,438
- Is it a four-syllable name?
- Jeez.

427
00:28:00,572 --> 00:28:02,505
Who is it? You know, right?

428
00:28:02,505 --> 00:28:03,638
I don't know, either.

429
00:28:03,638 --> 00:28:06,738
- You're lying, punk.
- Stop it.

430
00:28:06,738 --> 00:28:09,205
You follow Kang Tae Joo around all day.
How can you not know?

431
00:28:09,205 --> 00:28:11,305
I really don't know!

432
00:28:11,305 --> 00:28:13,449
Be straight with me.

433
00:28:13,449 --> 00:28:17,289
- Huh? Bluffing, right?
- What do you mean, bluffing?

434
00:28:18,121 --> 00:28:21,672
You know Park Ae Sook's purse
was found at the bookstore, right?

435
00:28:21,672 --> 00:28:24,005
This guy was the one who put it there.

436
00:28:24,005 --> 00:28:25,672
- What?
- Do you think that's all?

437
00:28:25,672 --> 00:28:29,405
He was also at the Lee Joo Hee
murder scene, they say.

438
00:28:31,072 --> 00:28:32,738
I should go.

439
00:28:39,305 --> 00:28:40,738
Is that true?

440
00:28:40,738 --> 00:28:43,038
Yes, that's what Detective Park said.

441
00:28:43,038 --> 00:28:46,305
- He was at the Lee Joo Hee murder scene too?
- Yes.

442
00:28:47,138 --> 00:28:49,405
That can't be.

443
00:28:49,405 --> 00:28:54,338
Back then, Detective Do and I were
searching the area to catch Lee Ki Beom.

444
00:28:54,338 --> 00:28:56,238
There wasn't anyone suspicious.

445
00:28:56,238 --> 00:28:59,038
Except for the limping guy.

446
00:28:59,038 --> 00:29:00,298
Wait.

447
00:29:00,298 --> 00:29:01,872
The limping guy?

448
00:29:01,872 --> 00:29:03,072
Yes.

449
00:29:03,072 --> 00:29:04,338
I only need to check just one thing.

450
00:29:04,338 --> 00:29:07,038
When you got stabbed,
did you see anything about the suspect?

451
00:29:07,038 --> 00:29:11,005
Like, was there anything
memorable about his walk?

452
00:29:11,638 --> 00:29:14,438
Why are you telling me this only now!

453
00:29:14,438 --> 00:29:17,538
- Who was it? Did you identify him?
- Well...

454
00:29:17,538 --> 00:29:19,238
You didn't?

455
00:29:20,172 --> 00:29:23,038
He just knows Lee Ki Beom so...

456
00:29:24,838 --> 00:29:26,205
He's an acquaintance of Lee Ki Beom?

457
00:29:26,205 --> 00:29:27,805
Yes.

458
00:29:28,585 --> 00:29:31,072
But please don't worry.

459
00:29:31,072 --> 00:29:35,072
- We made sure he keeps his mouth shut.
- I'm not asking about that. Who is he!

460
00:29:43,202 --> 00:29:46,372
[Kangseng Branch]

461
00:29:46,372 --> 00:29:50,072
When you were arrested,

462
00:29:50,072 --> 00:29:52,372
who saw you?

463
00:29:52,372 --> 00:29:54,538
I heard it's someone you know.

464
00:29:55,438 --> 00:29:57,205
I don't know.

465
00:29:59,038 --> 00:30:02,005
I think you've misunderstood something.

466
00:30:02,005 --> 00:30:06,372
Evidence has emerged suggesting
he might be the real killer.

467
00:30:06,372 --> 00:30:08,005
What do you mean?

468
00:30:08,005 --> 00:30:09,472
It's him!

469
00:30:09,472 --> 00:30:13,638
He's the one who placed
Park Ae Sook's purse in your bookstore.

470
00:30:13,638 --> 00:30:18,338
You know that purse is the decisive evidence
framing you as the real killer, right?

471
00:30:18,972 --> 00:30:21,705
That's why we're investigating you.

472
00:30:21,705 --> 00:30:23,081
Cooperate with us.

473
00:30:25,738 --> 00:30:30,538
Honestly, if he's the real killer,
isn't that good for you too?

474
00:30:32,105 --> 00:30:34,205
Name him.

475
00:30:34,205 --> 00:30:36,438
That guy can't be the one.

476
00:30:39,072 --> 00:30:41,405
- What?
- He's not the killer!

477
00:30:41,405 --> 00:30:42,838
You punk!

478
00:30:42,838 --> 00:30:46,438
The prosecutor is speaking. How dare you!

479
00:30:46,438 --> 00:30:48,772
- That's enough.
- I'll finish up shortly.

480
00:30:48,772 --> 00:30:51,172
Enough, enough!

481
00:30:52,638 --> 00:30:54,738
Get your head straight!

482
00:31:06,638 --> 00:31:09,505
It was the same back then too.

483
00:31:09,505 --> 00:31:12,972
They told me to name one fellow protester.

484
00:31:12,972 --> 00:31:15,172
And they'd let me go.

485
00:31:16,072 --> 00:31:20,138
They coaxed, soothed, hit, and threatened me.

486
00:31:20,138 --> 00:31:22,205
So I named him.

487
00:31:23,272 --> 00:31:27,638
I got out safely as promised,
but my friend...

488
00:31:29,572 --> 00:31:31,638
My friend didn't get out safely.

489
00:31:35,238 --> 00:31:38,372
I could never go back to the school

490
00:31:39,305 --> 00:31:41,838
where my friend never returned.

491
00:31:47,272 --> 00:31:51,205
I can't lose another friend like that.

492
00:31:59,738 --> 00:32:02,272
It looks like Detective Kang is
on a wild goose chase this time.

493
00:32:02,272 --> 00:32:04,772
He can't even walk properly.

494
00:32:04,772 --> 00:32:07,438
He's escaped multiple times,
but how could a limping man...

495
00:32:07,438 --> 00:32:10,038
No, no!

496
00:32:10,038 --> 00:32:12,505
Can't you see that?

497
00:32:12,505 --> 00:32:13,538
Pardon?

498
00:32:13,538 --> 00:32:15,138
Lee Ki Beom, that punk,

499
00:32:15,138 --> 00:32:18,205
if he's the killer, would he react like that?

500
00:32:23,205 --> 00:32:25,938
Is Lee Ki Beom really the killer?

501
00:32:33,805 --> 00:32:35,638
Ki Beom!

502
00:32:35,638 --> 00:32:36,805
Tae Joo!

503
00:32:36,805 --> 00:32:38,005
You can't.

504
00:32:38,005 --> 00:32:40,138
Visits are not allowed.

505
00:32:43,505 --> 00:32:45,472
We're family.

506
00:32:47,605 --> 00:32:49,972
[Police Officer ID: Kang Tae Joo]
We just need five minutes. Five minutes.

507
00:32:54,105 --> 00:32:56,272
Only five minutes.

508
00:33:04,938 --> 00:33:07,572
How are you feeling?

509
00:33:09,072 --> 00:33:11,272
I'm getting better.

510
00:33:16,672 --> 00:33:18,272
I'm sorry.

511
00:33:19,805 --> 00:33:22,905
Honestly, I suspected you.

512
00:33:22,905 --> 00:33:28,072
When I heard you followed Min Ji that day,
I thought maybe you did more than

513
00:33:28,072 --> 00:33:29,738
just gave her an umbrella.

514
00:33:33,538 --> 00:33:35,838
That's your job, right?

515
00:33:37,038 --> 00:33:39,172
I don't blame you.

516
00:33:43,672 --> 00:33:45,305
Tae Joo.

517
00:33:46,605 --> 00:33:48,972
I can get out, right?

518
00:33:52,038 --> 00:33:55,338
I need to get out
before Sun Young gives birth.

519
00:33:56,772 --> 00:33:59,172
By then, it'd be too late.

520
00:33:59,972 --> 00:34:03,138
Before Sun Young starts showing,

521
00:34:03,138 --> 00:34:05,205
you need to hold the wedding.

522
00:34:07,738 --> 00:34:09,372
Okay.

523
00:34:12,405 --> 00:34:15,605
[Italian Bakery]

524
00:34:18,205 --> 00:34:20,605
You must have been
shocked by the news, right?

525
00:34:21,938 --> 00:34:26,738
I never imagined Lee Ki Beom
would be illegally arrested.

526
00:34:26,738 --> 00:34:28,841
I'm ashamed as a prosecutor.

527
00:34:28,841 --> 00:34:30,572
No,

528
00:34:30,572 --> 00:34:33,405
you got injured while rescuing me
and were in the hospital.

529
00:34:33,405 --> 00:34:36,638
No, that can't be an excuse.

530
00:34:36,638 --> 00:34:38,972
I'll handle the investigation
properly from now on.

531
00:34:38,972 --> 00:34:42,238
Does that mean Ki Beom can be released?

532
00:34:42,238 --> 00:34:45,438
Fortunately, there's a witness.

533
00:34:45,438 --> 00:34:48,238
They say it's Lee Ki Beom's friend.
If we find him...

534
00:34:48,238 --> 00:34:51,738
Which of Ki Beom's friends
are you talking about?

535
00:34:51,738 --> 00:34:54,238
I don't really know his name, but,

536
00:34:54,238 --> 00:34:57,638
only that he has a leg problem.

537
00:34:58,605 --> 00:35:00,638
Im Seok Man?

538
00:35:01,772 --> 00:35:03,472
Seok Man?

539
00:35:03,472 --> 00:35:05,105
Who?

540
00:35:07,038 --> 00:35:08,405
Officer.

541
00:35:08,405 --> 00:35:11,472
Find out everything you can
about Im Seok Man right now.

542
00:35:11,472 --> 00:35:14,205
See if he has a criminal record
and what his blood type is.

543
00:35:14,205 --> 00:35:16,472
His blood type is B.

544
00:35:18,872 --> 00:35:21,072
He doesn't have a criminal record.

545
00:35:27,005 --> 00:35:29,372
You two, go grab some coffee for a bit.

546
00:35:29,372 --> 00:35:30,972
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

547
00:35:41,405 --> 00:35:43,038
What is this?

548
00:35:43,038 --> 00:35:47,738
Data comparing the suspect's body hair
found at the scene with that of Im Seok Man.

549
00:35:49,605 --> 00:35:50,805
Is that true?

550
00:35:50,805 --> 00:35:53,172
Yes, the suspect hair sample you sent

551
00:35:53,172 --> 00:35:55,572
also showed high levels
of titanium and sodium.

552
00:35:55,572 --> 00:35:56,638
It matches the killer.

553
00:35:56,638 --> 00:35:57,838
[Radioisotope Analysis Report]

554
00:35:57,838 --> 00:36:01,105
Radioisotope analysis?

555
00:36:01,105 --> 00:36:04,838
Is this it? Is this what you call
a scientific investigation technique?

556
00:36:04,838 --> 00:36:07,872
You wanted to know.

557
00:36:08,972 --> 00:36:10,089
Not the National Forensic Service

558
00:36:10,089 --> 00:36:12,138
but the Korea
Atomic Energy Research Institute?

559
00:36:12,838 --> 00:36:14,172
You see that?

560
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:16,772
[Korea Atomic Energy Research Institute]
The suspect is a laborer who sweats a lot,

561
00:36:16,772 --> 00:36:20,972
seemingly in a job like a welder
who works with metal.

562
00:36:20,972 --> 00:36:24,972
Im Seok Man fits this report perfectly.

563
00:36:24,972 --> 00:36:29,738
And the one who brought Park Ae Sook's purse
to Lee Ki Beom's bookstore

564
00:36:29,738 --> 00:36:31,672
was Im Seok Man.

565
00:36:33,905 --> 00:36:36,005
Do you think that's a coincidence?

566
00:36:37,238 --> 00:36:39,238
They said Im Seok Man can't even run.

567
00:36:39,238 --> 00:36:40,938
He can run.

568
00:36:41,672 --> 00:36:43,938
I saw it with my own eyes.

569
00:36:46,005 --> 00:36:48,038
This is driving me crazy.

570
00:36:51,272 --> 00:36:53,538
Changing suspects before trial?

571
00:36:53,538 --> 00:36:55,772
That's not a big deal.

572
00:36:55,772 --> 00:36:58,705
But once the trial begins,

573
00:36:58,705 --> 00:37:01,005
there's no turning back.

574
00:37:04,738 --> 00:37:09,305
He'll do anything to
avoid disappointing his father.

575
00:37:09,305 --> 00:37:13,738
If the suspect you indicted
is found not guilty,

576
00:37:13,738 --> 00:37:16,972
with your father's election coming up soon...

577
00:37:18,905 --> 00:37:21,105
Are you really okay with that?

578
00:37:25,805 --> 00:37:28,772
Seok Man's not here.

579
00:37:28,772 --> 00:37:30,705
Where did he go?

580
00:37:30,705 --> 00:37:33,105
I'm not sure. Did Seok Man go to work today?

581
00:37:33,105 --> 00:37:36,838
What work is there? No outside jobs today.

582
00:37:36,838 --> 00:37:40,072
He said he was going to meet his friend.

583
00:37:46,872 --> 00:37:48,538
Seok Man!

584
00:37:51,038 --> 00:37:53,438
What are you doing here at this hour?

585
00:37:53,438 --> 00:37:55,105
Well...

586
00:37:55,805 --> 00:37:58,372
I have something to return to you.

587
00:38:01,438 --> 00:38:03,105
What friend?

588
00:38:03,105 --> 00:38:07,138
I don't know. He said
he was returning a handkerchief.

589
00:38:07,138 --> 00:38:09,305
Is this it?

590
00:38:09,305 --> 00:38:12,138
Hey, this isn't yours!

591
00:38:13,738 --> 00:38:17,638
Hey, can I take a look at it?

592
00:38:40,338 --> 00:38:42,805
What is it?

593
00:38:42,805 --> 00:38:44,738
A handkerchief.

594
00:38:44,738 --> 00:38:46,772
A handkerchief?

595
00:38:47,605 --> 00:38:50,072
You mean Ki Beom's handkerchief?

596
00:38:50,072 --> 00:38:51,272
Yeah.

597
00:38:51,272 --> 00:38:53,938
Why do you have that?

598
00:38:53,938 --> 00:38:56,805
Ki Beom seemed to have left it at my place.

599
00:38:56,805 --> 00:38:58,505
When exactly was that?

600
00:38:58,505 --> 00:38:59,913
Well...

601
00:39:00,605 --> 00:39:03,072
- I'm not sure.
- Think carefully.

602
00:39:03,072 --> 00:39:05,405
Since when was it there?

603
00:39:05,405 --> 00:39:07,205
I don't really remember.

604
00:39:09,838 --> 00:39:13,172
Where is it now? Is it at your house?

605
00:39:13,172 --> 00:39:15,972
- Yeah.
- Let's go to your house.

606
00:39:15,972 --> 00:39:17,572
Now?

607
00:39:18,472 --> 00:39:20,305
What are you doing? Hurry up.

608
00:39:20,305 --> 00:39:22,205
Okay.

609
00:39:27,838 --> 00:39:29,838
Sun Young, slow down a bit.

610
00:39:29,838 --> 00:39:32,472
Hurry up. We don't have time.

611
00:39:32,472 --> 00:39:36,372
Are you mad at me?
Because of the handkerchief?

612
00:39:38,472 --> 00:39:40,705
That too, and...

613
00:39:41,505 --> 00:39:43,738
You saw Ki Beom getting arrested, right?

614
00:39:43,738 --> 00:39:45,038
Why didn't you say anything?

615
00:39:45,038 --> 00:39:48,238
You knew I was looking for Ki Beom, so why?

616
00:39:48,238 --> 00:39:50,105
I...

617
00:39:50,105 --> 00:39:52,538
I really thought

618
00:39:52,538 --> 00:39:55,205
Ki Beom was the killer.

619
00:39:55,205 --> 00:39:56,605
What?

620
00:39:56,605 --> 00:40:00,038
Otherwise, the police wouldn't
have arrested him so forcefully.

621
00:40:00,038 --> 00:40:02,905
How could you suspect Ki Beom?

622
00:40:02,905 --> 00:40:04,438
You know him better than anyone.

623
00:40:04,438 --> 00:40:06,005
But the police back then were so...

624
00:40:06,005 --> 00:40:08,005
Do you think everything
the police do is right?

625
00:40:08,005 --> 00:40:10,072
Do you really believe that?

626
00:40:10,072 --> 00:40:13,172
There are innocent people
in this world, many of them!

627
00:40:13,172 --> 00:40:15,372
Ki Beom is one of them!

628
00:40:15,372 --> 00:40:17,905
It's all because of that handkerchief!

629
00:40:20,505 --> 00:40:23,738
You really don't remember
when it first showed up at your place?

630
00:40:26,305 --> 00:40:27,905
Well...

631
00:40:29,905 --> 00:40:33,805
Ji Won was hospitalized
on the same day as me, so...

632
00:40:33,805 --> 00:40:35,072
September 7th!

633
00:40:35,072 --> 00:40:37,138
Was it before or after that?

634
00:40:38,738 --> 00:40:41,972
- I don't really remember...
- Don't just say you don't remember.

635
00:40:41,972 --> 00:40:44,172
Try to think carefully.

636
00:40:46,105 --> 00:40:47,672
Maybe before?

637
00:40:47,672 --> 00:40:50,605
Before? Are you sure?

638
00:40:51,372 --> 00:40:52,705
Then what happens?

639
00:40:52,705 --> 00:40:54,105
What else?

640
00:40:54,105 --> 00:40:56,805
It means he can clear his name!

641
00:40:57,905 --> 00:41:01,505
After Ki Beom lost it,
the killer must have had it,

642
00:41:01,505 --> 00:41:05,572
so the killer isn't Ki Beom but the one
who had that handkerchief at the time...

643
00:41:30,738 --> 00:41:32,438
Sun Young.

644
00:41:34,338 --> 00:41:36,472
Don't come any closer!

645
00:41:42,605 --> 00:41:44,305
Don't tell me

646
00:41:46,038 --> 00:41:48,105
the killer

647
00:41:48,105 --> 00:41:49,805
is you?

648
00:41:50,805 --> 00:41:52,805
What?

649
00:41:52,805 --> 00:41:54,705
Answer me!

650
00:41:57,905 --> 00:42:01,638
You... How could you...

651
00:42:01,638 --> 00:42:04,872
You trust Ki Beom that much,
but why not me...

652
00:42:06,738 --> 00:42:08,405
Sun Young, are you okay?

653
00:42:08,405 --> 00:42:09,772
Stay back!

654
00:42:09,772 --> 00:42:12,005
Don't come near me!

655
00:42:12,005 --> 00:42:15,805
Why are you acting like this? What did I do?

656
00:42:15,805 --> 00:42:17,472
Sun Young!

657
00:42:29,905 --> 00:42:31,638
Sun Young!

658
00:42:36,372 --> 00:42:39,038
Im Seok Man, you punk!

659
00:42:39,038 --> 00:42:41,105
- Sun Young, are you okay?
- Im Seok Man!

660
00:42:43,405 --> 00:42:45,205
Are you alright?

661
00:42:46,072 --> 00:42:51,205
You are under arrest
as a serial murder suspect.

662
00:42:51,205 --> 00:42:55,672
No, it's not me!

663
00:42:59,005 --> 00:43:00,705
Stop this!

664
00:43:03,205 --> 00:43:05,005
It really wasn't me.

665
00:43:05,005 --> 00:43:07,172
Why would I ever kill anyone?

666
00:43:07,172 --> 00:43:09,038
Why would I...

667
00:43:11,305 --> 00:43:13,738
Then what is this?

668
00:43:13,738 --> 00:43:16,038
How did this end up with you?

669
00:43:16,038 --> 00:43:17,672
That's...

670
00:43:18,972 --> 00:43:21,372
I have no idea.

671
00:43:22,038 --> 00:43:25,105
Obviously Ki Beom must've dropped it.

672
00:43:25,105 --> 00:43:26,538
That's just how he is.

673
00:43:26,538 --> 00:43:31,638
He says it's precious, but then
he just drops things like that.

674
00:43:32,605 --> 00:43:36,905
After all the efforts Sun Young
put into making it...

675
00:43:39,872 --> 00:43:43,172
There are a few guys who pick fights
with Ki Beom sometimes.

676
00:43:43,172 --> 00:43:47,838
They say he flirts with all the women
in the neighborhood.

677
00:43:47,838 --> 00:43:52,772
I guess they're jealous
because Ki Beom is so popular.

678
00:43:55,405 --> 00:43:57,238
So,

679
00:43:59,305 --> 00:44:01,505
you like Sun Young, huh?

680
00:44:02,272 --> 00:44:04,772
That's why you hate Ki Beom?

681
00:44:04,772 --> 00:44:06,005
Because Ki Beom likes Sun Young?

682
00:44:06,005 --> 00:44:08,472
I liked her first!

683
00:44:08,472 --> 00:44:09,838
What?

684
00:44:09,838 --> 00:44:12,405
I said I liked her first.

685
00:44:18,805 --> 00:44:21,672
- Whoa.
- It's just like mine.

686
00:44:21,672 --> 00:44:23,505
It's really pretty.

687
00:44:25,672 --> 00:44:28,872
I made this myself.

688
00:44:28,872 --> 00:44:31,738
- Really?
- Yeah.

689
00:44:31,738 --> 00:44:33,338
Thanks.

690
00:44:37,572 --> 00:44:39,538
I've got something for you too.

691
00:44:39,538 --> 00:44:41,205
Something for me?

692
00:44:43,072 --> 00:44:44,972
Close your eyes.

693
00:45:14,205 --> 00:45:17,072
Even though he knew I liked her,

694
00:45:18,438 --> 00:45:21,605
he still confessed to Sun Young.

695
00:45:23,205 --> 00:45:25,372
What kind of friend does that?

696
00:45:25,372 --> 00:45:27,838
They've spent so much time together,

697
00:45:27,838 --> 00:45:30,938
and you just barged in like that, you punk.

698
00:45:31,605 --> 00:45:34,938
You planted that purse
to frame Ki Beom, didn't you?

699
00:45:34,938 --> 00:45:36,705
No.

700
00:45:36,705 --> 00:45:37,872
That's not true, Tae Joo!

701
00:45:37,872 --> 00:45:39,538
Don't call me that!

702
00:45:44,505 --> 00:45:47,338
It's disgusting and terrifying
that someone like you

703
00:45:47,338 --> 00:45:49,805
was around my family.

704
00:45:49,805 --> 00:45:52,905
Do you know how many people
died because of you?

705
00:45:53,738 --> 00:45:55,872
And you still call yourself human?

706
00:45:58,672 --> 00:45:59,705
Tae Joo...

707
00:45:59,705 --> 00:46:02,505
Say my name again,

708
00:46:02,505 --> 00:46:05,105
and I'll tear your mouth open.

709
00:46:10,705 --> 00:46:13,138
Confess and repent as soon as possible.

710
00:46:13,138 --> 00:46:17,972
Spend the rest of your life
atoning for those you killed.

711
00:46:27,405 --> 00:46:29,972
Over the past two years in Kangseng,

712
00:46:29,972 --> 00:46:34,272
seven women were murdered
in the Kangseng Serial Murder Case.

713
00:46:34,272 --> 00:46:37,605
The suspect has finally been arrested.

714
00:46:37,605 --> 00:46:39,538
How did you manage to arrest the suspect?

715
00:46:39,538 --> 00:46:43,838
We found the item used in the crime
at the suspect's residence,

716
00:46:43,838 --> 00:46:47,705
and through radioactive isotope analysis
by the Atomic Energy Research Institute,

717
00:46:47,705 --> 00:46:50,705
we confirmed the suspect is the killer.

718
00:46:50,705 --> 00:46:54,038
So you're certain
he's the real killer this time?

719
00:46:54,038 --> 00:46:57,505
Yes, we're certain.

720
00:47:00,873 --> 00:47:04,238
Huh? What's all this?

721
00:47:04,238 --> 00:47:05,805
Are we having a feast?

722
00:47:05,805 --> 00:47:07,038
Ji Won!

723
00:47:07,038 --> 00:47:08,338
Ji Won, you're here.

724
00:47:08,338 --> 00:47:09,605
You too, hurry up and help.

725
00:47:09,605 --> 00:47:12,538
There's still a ton to do.

726
00:47:12,538 --> 00:47:14,572
You're missing the most important thing.

727
00:47:14,572 --> 00:47:18,005
For someone just out of jail,
nothing beats tofu.

728
00:47:18,005 --> 00:47:19,072
Tofu? Come on.

729
00:47:19,072 --> 00:47:20,772
On a day like this, we should give him meat.

730
00:47:20,772 --> 00:47:22,172
Jeez, ma'am.

731
00:47:22,172 --> 00:47:26,572
He needs to eat this
so he doesn't end up going back there.

732
00:47:26,572 --> 00:47:29,072
Bring it here. I'll cook it.

733
00:47:29,872 --> 00:47:32,457
When is Ki Beom coming back?

734
00:47:33,638 --> 00:47:34,665
Ki Hwan went to pick him up,

735
00:47:34,665 --> 00:47:36,838
- so he'll be here soon.
- Oh.

736
00:47:54,672 --> 00:47:57,305
Everyone's waiting for you at home.

737
00:47:57,305 --> 00:47:59,438
Sun Young is there too.

738
00:47:59,438 --> 00:48:00,872
She is?

739
00:48:00,872 --> 00:48:04,638
Mom gave you two her permission.

740
00:48:04,638 --> 00:48:06,638
Is that true?

741
00:48:06,638 --> 00:48:08,438
But, how...

742
00:48:08,438 --> 00:48:11,138
Sun Young really went through a lot.

743
00:48:13,638 --> 00:48:15,938
I can't wait to see everyone.

744
00:48:21,872 --> 00:48:23,572
Hey, what's wrong?

745
00:48:25,072 --> 00:48:26,572
I'm just a little hungry.

746
00:48:26,572 --> 00:48:28,172
Oh, man.

747
00:48:28,172 --> 00:48:30,372
You must be starving.

748
00:48:30,372 --> 00:48:32,672
The food in detention center
can't be any good, right?

749
00:48:32,672 --> 00:48:35,938
Mom actually prepared a lot of food for you.

750
00:48:35,938 --> 00:48:37,305
Oh, right!

751
00:48:37,305 --> 00:48:39,938
Your sister-in-law told us to get a cake.

752
00:48:39,938 --> 00:48:42,538
Your birthday has already passed.

753
00:48:42,538 --> 00:48:44,972
What cake?

754
00:48:44,972 --> 00:48:46,038
Let's just go straight home.

755
00:48:46,038 --> 00:48:48,905
No, it'll only take a minute.

756
00:48:52,405 --> 00:48:54,038
- Ki Hwan.
- Yeah?

757
00:48:54,038 --> 00:48:55,538
I'm gonna sleep for a bit.

758
00:48:55,538 --> 00:48:58,272
Yeah, sure. Sleep comfortably.

759
00:48:58,272 --> 00:49:01,338
I'll wake you up once we're home.

760
00:49:18,472 --> 00:49:20,538
Ki Beom.

761
00:49:20,538 --> 00:49:23,605
Ki Beom, wake up! You're home.

762
00:49:31,438 --> 00:49:33,538
Look at your bruised face.

763
00:49:33,538 --> 00:49:35,838
You've been through a lot, right?

764
00:49:43,238 --> 00:49:46,138
I thought I'd never see you again.

765
00:49:46,138 --> 00:49:48,238
Don't say that.

766
00:49:49,105 --> 00:49:53,372
I'm really glad you came back safe.

767
00:50:01,372 --> 00:50:03,272
Sun Young.

768
00:50:05,905 --> 00:50:07,572
Let's live

769
00:50:08,605 --> 00:50:10,772
like normal people now.

770
00:50:27,105 --> 00:50:30,905
Get married like others,

771
00:50:32,438 --> 00:50:36,772
have kids like others,

772
00:50:38,905 --> 00:50:41,338
and grow old together.

773
00:50:43,938 --> 00:50:46,729
Just like everyone else.

774
00:51:06,738 --> 00:51:09,105
Just like

775
00:51:09,105 --> 00:51:10,872
everyone else...

776
00:51:23,405 --> 00:51:25,205
Hey, Ki Beom, I went in

777
00:51:25,205 --> 00:51:28,272
and saw your favorite cake right there, so...

778
00:51:30,772 --> 00:51:32,372
Are you sleeping?

779
00:51:35,438 --> 00:51:37,038
Ki Beom?

780
00:51:38,572 --> 00:51:40,238
Ki Beom!

781
00:51:41,805 --> 00:51:43,538
What's wrong with you?

782
00:51:43,538 --> 00:51:45,638
Hey, Ki Beom!

783
00:51:45,638 --> 00:51:48,005
Hey, hey... Ki Beom!

784
00:51:48,938 --> 00:51:50,872
Hey, Ki Beom!

785
00:51:50,872 --> 00:51:53,372
Ki Beom, snap out of it!

786
00:51:53,372 --> 00:51:55,272
Ki Beom...

787
00:51:56,772 --> 00:51:58,538
Ki Beom!

788
00:51:58,538 --> 00:52:00,505
What's wrong with you?

789
00:52:00,505 --> 00:52:02,405
Hey!

790
00:52:09,238 --> 00:52:11,005
Ki Beom!

791
00:52:11,005 --> 00:52:15,338
[Stop]

792
00:52:20,772 --> 00:52:25,538
[Murderer, get out
Condolences]

793
00:52:35,738 --> 00:52:38,438
Look over there. That's Kang Tae Joo, right?

794
00:52:38,438 --> 00:52:40,105
Yeah, that's him.

795
00:52:40,105 --> 00:52:41,605
That punk took Ki Beom away.

796
00:52:41,605 --> 00:52:43,505
- Oh, dear.
- How shameless.

797
00:52:43,505 --> 00:52:45,738
How dare you even show your face here?

798
00:53:04,738 --> 00:53:06,405
Tae Joo...

799
00:53:10,672 --> 00:53:13,105
Where is Ki Beom?

800
00:53:15,505 --> 00:53:18,438
You killed him.

801
00:53:18,438 --> 00:53:21,172
You killed him!

802
00:53:21,172 --> 00:53:24,105
Ki Beom...

803
00:53:24,105 --> 00:53:26,538
I'm... I'm sorry.

804
00:53:27,572 --> 00:53:29,572
Bring him back!

805
00:53:29,572 --> 00:53:35,805
Bring my precious boy back to me!

806
00:53:35,805 --> 00:53:39,972
My sweet, kind boy...

807
00:53:39,972 --> 00:53:43,905
My precious boy...

808
00:53:43,905 --> 00:53:48,438
Bring him back!

809
00:53:48,438 --> 00:53:54,105
Bring him back! Bring him back!

810
00:53:56,472 --> 00:53:58,238
Take her inside.

811
00:54:13,505 --> 00:54:15,172
Ki Hwan...

812
00:54:17,572 --> 00:54:21,238
I have something to say to Ki Beom.

813
00:54:21,238 --> 00:54:23,138
I'm sorry!

814
00:54:25,638 --> 00:54:28,305
But I can't see you anymore.

815
00:54:29,038 --> 00:54:31,005
Please just go.

816
00:54:37,472 --> 00:54:39,238
Ki Hwan...

817
00:54:41,072 --> 00:54:42,838
Go.

818
00:55:13,338 --> 00:55:17,738
They said it was sepsis
caused by organ failure.

819
00:55:17,738 --> 00:55:21,072
It seems his condition
was already serious in detention.

820
00:55:21,738 --> 00:55:25,172
Even the guards told him to
go to the hospital first after release.

821
00:55:26,305 --> 00:55:28,738
How could a perfectly healthy person

822
00:55:29,538 --> 00:55:31,738
end up like this overnight?

823
00:55:34,838 --> 00:55:36,605
I...

824
00:55:39,172 --> 00:55:41,905
I did this. It was me.

825
00:55:41,905 --> 00:55:44,772
I ruined everything.

826
00:55:44,772 --> 00:55:46,738
I...

827
00:55:49,238 --> 00:55:51,472
killed Ki Beom.

828
00:55:51,472 --> 00:55:52,505
Tae Joo.

829
00:55:52,505 --> 00:55:54,072
- I...
- Tae Joo.

830
00:55:54,072 --> 00:55:56,672
Look at me. Look at me!

831
00:55:57,872 --> 00:56:00,405
You can't fall apart now.

832
00:56:00,405 --> 00:56:04,572
We have to make those punks
who did that to Ki Beom pay.

833
00:56:04,572 --> 00:56:07,172
None of them even came to the funeral.

834
00:56:07,172 --> 00:56:09,838
No one is even asking for forgiveness.

835
00:56:11,338 --> 00:56:13,938
How can people be like this?

836
00:56:41,672 --> 00:56:42,905
Where is Cha Si Young?

837
00:56:42,905 --> 00:56:45,572
He went to a funeral.

838
00:56:45,572 --> 00:56:47,372
A funeral?

839
00:56:49,005 --> 00:56:50,772
That punk?

840
00:56:51,977 --> 00:56:54,207
[Condolences]

841
00:57:02,305 --> 00:57:05,672
- Assemblyman!
- Oh my, it's been a while.

842
00:57:05,672 --> 00:57:07,905
Take it easy.

843
00:57:07,905 --> 00:57:12,945
- It's been so long.
- How do you do?

844
00:57:39,272 --> 00:57:40,905
Ki Beom...

845
00:57:43,805 --> 00:57:46,172
This place is like a festival.

846
00:58:01,338 --> 00:58:03,972
Without any guilt,

847
00:58:06,872 --> 00:58:09,672
or any sorrow,

848
00:58:11,705 --> 00:58:15,172
they just laugh and chatter.

849
00:58:38,605 --> 00:58:41,638
To those who caused your death,

850
00:58:43,305 --> 00:58:45,238
you've already

851
00:58:46,638 --> 00:58:48,572
been forgotten.

852
00:59:28,638 --> 00:59:31,472
So don't forgive anyone.

853
00:59:32,538 --> 00:59:35,072
Even me,

854
00:59:35,072 --> 00:59:37,605
who is helplessly kneeling

855
00:59:39,672 --> 00:59:41,672
before them.

856
00:59:46,105 --> 00:59:48,138
Have you

857
00:59:48,138 --> 00:59:52,538
ever been found out as the killer?

858
00:59:55,172 --> 00:59:57,038
I guess not.

859
00:59:57,038 --> 01:00:00,905
If I had, I wouldn't have gotten away
with it this long, right?

860
01:00:00,905 --> 01:00:03,672
Don't you agree?

861
01:00:05,472 --> 01:00:07,538
What about Ki Beom?

862
01:00:10,538 --> 01:00:12,338
Did Ki Beom

863
01:00:13,038 --> 01:00:17,172
know you were the killer?

864
01:00:24,572 --> 01:00:28,272
No, he didn't.

865
01:00:37,538 --> 01:00:41,172
Ki Beom, I'll buy you a cake, so just wait...

866
01:00:43,438 --> 01:00:45,472
Hey, Ki Beom, what's wrong?

867
01:00:46,738 --> 01:00:47,938
Are you hurt somewhere?

868
01:00:47,938 --> 01:00:49,938
Why are you like this?

869
01:00:55,938 --> 01:00:57,905
What's wrong with you?

870
01:00:58,605 --> 01:01:01,405
- Ki Hwan...
- Oh dear.

871
01:01:01,405 --> 01:01:03,338
This isn't good.
We should go to the hospital.

872
01:01:03,338 --> 01:01:05,105
Did you do that?

873
01:01:05,105 --> 01:01:06,772
What?

874
01:01:06,772 --> 01:01:08,838
You told Tae Joo

875
01:01:11,105 --> 01:01:13,638
that I followed Min Ji out?

876
01:01:15,038 --> 01:01:16,305
Huh?

877
01:01:16,305 --> 01:01:20,372
That wasn't me. It was you.

878
01:01:24,838 --> 01:01:26,772
It's raining!

879
01:01:31,172 --> 01:01:32,238
This won't do.

880
01:01:32,238 --> 01:01:35,805
I'll bring her an umbrella and then go home.
You just lock up and go.

881
01:01:35,805 --> 01:01:37,572
Don't touch this! I'll deal with it tomorrow.

882
01:01:37,572 --> 01:01:38,872
[Umbrella, 600 won]
Got it.

883
01:01:38,872 --> 01:01:43,438
You said you'd bring Min Ji an umbrella

884
01:01:43,438 --> 01:01:45,372
and followed her out, right?

885
01:01:52,172 --> 01:01:54,038
Did I?

886
01:01:55,905 --> 01:01:58,938
You just got confused, huh?

887
01:02:04,305 --> 01:02:06,038
Of course.

888
01:02:06,705 --> 01:02:09,038
What other reason would there be?

889
01:02:10,738 --> 01:02:12,872
You need to get to a hospital.

890
01:02:24,838 --> 01:02:26,605
Ki Beom...

891
01:02:27,272 --> 01:02:29,038
Ki Hwan.

892
01:02:31,372 --> 01:02:33,405
Don't touch Sun Young,

893
01:02:34,972 --> 01:02:36,805
no matter what.

894
01:02:41,472 --> 01:02:43,472
Mark my words.

895
01:03:55,705 --> 01:03:57,838
I need to go get the cake.

896
01:03:58,505 --> 01:04:00,605
Just wait a little!

897
01:04:02,605 --> 01:04:04,538
Ki Beom

898
01:04:05,638 --> 01:04:08,172
knew nothing.

899
01:04:19,372 --> 01:04:22,205
So Ki Beom knew, huh?

900
01:04:28,738 --> 01:04:31,305
I said he didn't know.

901
01:04:37,638 --> 01:04:40,538
Why won't you believe me?

902
01:04:45,072 --> 01:04:48,572
It doesn't mean you're certain

903
01:04:48,572 --> 01:04:50,872
that he didn't know.

904
01:04:53,938 --> 01:04:56,238
It's still only an assumption.

905
01:05:09,138 --> 01:05:11,038
Lee Ki Hwan!

906
01:05:14,672 --> 01:05:16,738
Sit.

907
01:05:16,738 --> 01:05:18,972
Let's talk more.

908
01:05:24,905 --> 01:05:26,638
That name.

909
01:05:29,105 --> 01:05:31,605
It's been a long time since I've heard that.

910
01:05:48,605 --> 01:05:51,805
Now you're starting to
sound like the Tae Joo I knew.

911
01:06:32,972 --> 01:06:34,005
Now, move aside.

912
01:06:34,005 --> 01:06:37,072
We seek the death penalty,
the maximum sentence under the law.

913
01:06:37,072 --> 01:06:38,238
Are you still human?

914
01:06:38,238 --> 01:06:40,572
How could you frame me with that accusation?

915
01:06:40,572 --> 01:06:43,638
Seok Man, did you really kill them?
Those women...

916
01:06:43,638 --> 01:06:44,738
I killed them...

917
01:06:44,738 --> 01:06:47,638
Tae Joo, let's never see each other again.

918
01:06:47,638 --> 01:06:49,538
This is... Sun Young! Kang Sun Young!

919
01:06:49,538 --> 01:06:51,905
I think Sun Young is trying to kill herself.

920
01:06:51,905 --> 01:06:52,938
How can we give up?

921
01:06:52,938 --> 01:06:55,605
One person is dead,
and the other is falsely accused.

922
01:06:55,605 --> 01:06:57,938
Sun Young, it's dangerous! Come down!
